Impromptu market and bread shopping @dupainetdesidees - picked up beautiful fresh strawberries, asparagus and tomatoes as well as terrine, rabbit (!) and more! (And if you have Alexa enabled, apologies if my IG Live turned it on. I’ve been resisting using it but thought I’d finally give it a try when I bought a new speaker that included it…and she decided to start playing music during the video, and some commenters said me talking about it turned their “Alexas” on too😅😁) What do you look forward to most at the market in the summer?

I’ve been eyeing The New Pie cookbook by @floursugarbutter since I first read about their prize-winning pies (and their personal story💯) in the @nytimes and had bookmarked their Smoky Caramel Almond Pie for a while, and finally got around to making it. (With those ingredients, I’m wondering why I waited so long??) It’s chock-full of almonds and dulce de leche with a caramelized white chocolate topping and a few belts of single-malt scotch, and yes - it was worth the wait. It’s rich, nutty, caramel-y, and just the thing to get me back on the blogging bandwagon after summer vacation (and thankfully, swimsuit season is *finally* over…😅) Check out my new blog post and adapted recipe!
.
The link🔗is in my profile @davidlebovitz - tap on the link there, then the pic of this pie
.
